> Smoky and spicy with a slightly sweet kick, this peri peri seasoning gives any dish a tasty boost. This seasoning mix contains herbs and spices such as smoked paprika, ancho chilli powder, ground cumin and oregano, making its punchy taste perfect for marinating meat and fish, as well as a flavour driver in fried rice and loaded wedges.

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%grams}.

Once boiled, pour the water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%grams}, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} (no oil) on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%grams}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

While the pork cooks, open the remaining @Peri Peri Seasoning{1%sachet}.

Add the @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, peri peri seasoning, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Black Beans{1%carton} and liquid from the tin to the pork. Cook for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and stir through the @Mango Chutney{40%grams} and @Butter{20%grams}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of @Water{} if it's a little too thick.

Share rice between serving #bowls{}.

Top with the peri peri pork and sprinkle over the cheese.

Enjoy!